Package org.ietf.nea.pb.validate.rules

IETF TNCCS message validation rules.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AccessRecommendation
    Rule, that checks if access recommendation ID is known.
    AssessmentResult
    Rule, that checks if assessment result ID is known.
    BatchDirectionality
    Rule, that checks if the batch direction ID is known.
    BatchDirectionAndType
    Rule, that checks if the batch type and the batch direction correlate.
    BatchResultWithoutMessageAssessmentResult
    Rule, that checks if batch is result batch and contains assessment result.
    BatchType
    Rule, that checks if batch type ID is known.
    BatchVersion
    Rule, that checks if given batch version is supported.
    CommonLengthLimits
    Rule, that checks if a given length value is within common limits.
    ErrorCodeLimits
    Rule, that checks if error code is known and in range.
    ErrorVendorIdLimits
    Rule, that checks if error vendor ID is in range.
    ImIdLimits
    Rule, that checks if an IM(C/V) ID is in range.
    ImMessageTypeReservedAndLimits
    Rule, that checks if the integrity measurement component type ID is reserved or not in range.
    ImVendorIdReservedAndLimits
    Rule, that checks if the integrity measurement component vendor ID is reserved or not in range.
    LangCodeStringLimit
    Rule, that checks if an RFC 4646 language code string is to large.
    MinMessageLength
    Rule, that checks if the given length satisfies the minimum message length requirement.
    NoNullTerminatedString
    Rule, that checks if string is not terminated with null.
    NoSkipOnUnknownMessage
    Rule, that checks if no skip flag is set in the set of flags.
    NoZeroString
    Rule, that checks if string contains zero characters.
    PbMessageNoSkip
    Rule, that checks if a message needs a no skip flag and the no skip.
    TypeReservedAndLimits
    Rule, that checks if the message type ID is reserved or not in range.
    UriSyntax
    Rule, that checks if an URI string has a valid syntax.
    VendorIdReservedAndLimits
    Rule, that checks if the message vendor ID is reserved or not in range.
